{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 When you are using RIA, some files will be on the Server, and others on the Client. You will need to move them back and forth.\par
\par
In this example, there is an example of each. When you press the Server File to Client button, you will be able to copy a "Server" file to a "Client location.\par
\par
When you press "Client file to Server", you can do the reverse.\par
\par
Note that since you are probably running in the Studio, the "Client" and "Server" are probably the same physical machine.\par
}

{\rtf1\fbidis\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;\red255\green0\blue128;}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\ltrpar\cf1\b\f0\fs20 Here, you can move a server file to the client, using \cf2 ServerFileToClient()\cf1 . \par
\par
Note that only a limited number of server files are displayed. For security reasons, there is no generic function to browse all the Server files, as there is for the Client.\par
\par
After the function executes, the location of the copied file is displayed. The location is the application cache folder on the client. After the file is copied to the client, you can use the \cf2 ClientFileCopy()\cf1  function to copy it to another location.\par
}

{\rtf1\fbidis\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;\red255\green0\blue128;}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\ltrpar\cf1\b\f0\fs20 Here, you can copy a Client file to the Server, using \cf2 ClientFileToServer()\cf1 . \par
\par
The user can zoom on the Client file (or press the '...' button) to choose any client file.\par
\par
When \cf2 Copy File\cf1  is pressed, the file will be copied to a location on the Server. From there, you may choose to copy it to some other location as needed.\par
}
